On Sunday, June 7, Governor Cuomo announced that the deadline for submission of completed School District Budget vote ballots by mail has been changed to Tuesday, June 16.

Qualified voters who would like to submit their completed ballot in person can still do so from 9:00 am to 5:00 pm on Monday, June 8 and Tuesday, June 9 at the Elementary School and the High School.

We will share any further information when we receive it from the Governor’s Office.

post_text:
Did you know that the 2020-2021 proposed School District budget provides for the removal of the rubberized flooring system in the Elementary School's 1994 Gym and replacement with a wood flooring system, while using reserve funds at no additional cost to our taxpayers? The State Education Department requires voter approval before removal and replacement of the gym floor can move forward.

To learn more about the recent discovery of a safety concern regarding the current gym floor, and the District's plan for removal and replacement of the floor, please click here:

https://www.swcsd.org/cms/lib/NY02211678/Centricity/ModuleInstance/1605/Parent%20Communication%20and%20QuEST%20Report%201994%20Gym%20Floor.pdf

Dear Parents and Students,

I have GREAT NEWS for you! The yearbook is finished and is being printed as I type this email! They will arrive at our school this spring and at that time, we will communicate to you how and when to pick yours up.

Since this year is certainly one that will be remembered for the current events, be sure you don't forget about all of the wonderful events and memories of SULLIVAN WEST HIGH SCHOOL's entire 2019-2020 school year that the yearbook staff has worked so tirelessly to chronicle in this year's yearbook. I understand that there still are a handful of limited-edition copies available and you can order yours here: http://jostensyearbooks.com?ref=A01054562

Stay healthy and stay safe,

Ms. Scardino

Attention all 6th grade parents who participated in the Gertrude Hawk Chocolate fundraiser:

Your orders will NOT be ready for pick up today, Tuesday, April 7th between the hours of 2:00 p.m. and 6:00 p.m. as originally planned. Unfortunately, the shipping company changed the date without notifying us. Pick up will now be Thursday, 4/9 from 2 - 6pm.

Again, we ask you to use the 38’ parking lot entrance, to stay in your car, and follow the signs. You will not need to come into the building. We will bring your order out to you.

We are sorry for any inconvenience. If you have any questions regarding this pick up please contact Mrs. Humleker via the Remind app or by email: humlekercin@swcsd.org.

post_text:
For all of us, this is an uncertain time, filled with unanswered questions and concerns about what will come next. However, for our High School Seniors in the Class of 2020, this is also a time which impacts some of the final memories that they will make as students in our School District. The Class of 2020, lead by Clarissa Lewis and the Bulldog Bytes team, created and edited this video as a way of sharing with all of us what they miss about being away from school, their reflections on their time as Sullivan West Bulldogs, and what will come next for each of them.

We are so proud to know these exceptional young people, and privileged to have them as part of our community. To the Class of 2020 - we miss you, and we promise to find ways to honor your wonderful legacy and make more memories this Spring!

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HTCxNT23EvU&t=0s

A Message From The Class of 2020 - YouTube

The class of 2020 is trying their hardest to stay positive throughout all of this. This video is reminiscent of our past years in high school, and shows why ...

Good Evening, Bulldog Families:

Sullivan County Manager Josh Potosek has issued an Emergency Order closing all schools in Sullivan County, effective immediately and lasting through April 3. As a result, Sullivan West Schools are closed to students through April 3.

We will be sharing more information about our District's response to this mandated closure in the upcoming days.

Until then, please be safe, Bulldogs.

Please see the message below from Sullivan BOCES regarding the Countywide Elementary and Middle School Art Show Opening.

Out of an abundance of caution to not have large group gatherings, we have decided to cancel the Countywide Elementary & Middle School Art Show Opening. post_text:
In this season of giving, we are particularly proud to announce that our Elementary School's Kindness and Compassion (KC) Club, as well as the Western Sullivan United Teachers (WSUT) and School Related Professionals (SRP), partnered with the Western Sullivan Public Library to support their participation in the Great Give Back Event last month. The Public Library received 6 full boxes of food from our generous community, and they donated the food to our School District for distribution to local families. The Public Library also received donations of pet food and supplies, which the KC Club will provide to local animal shelters.

"Many thanks to our generous and caring community. We hope to make this an annual event," shared Audra Everett, Director of the Western Sullivan Public Library.

Thank you to all of our wonderful faculty, staff and students who helped in this amazing cause, to the Western Sullivan Public Library, and to our entire School District community for your generous support of our local families.

post_text:
Sullivan West Schools have “gone to the dogs”, in a good way! This year, both of our schools are welcoming trained therapy dogs in to spend time with our students on a regular basis. This initiative is part of our ongoing effort to meet the social and emotional needs of our students, so that they can be prepared to learn.

The Elementary School’s therapy dog, Sparkle (“Spark” for short) and her trainer, Julie Franke, visits classrooms each week and spends time with the students as they read, joins them on the classroom carpet as they learn, and helps to bring smiles to their faces! The High School’s therapy dog, Keeper, and his trainer, retired Social Worker Nancy Ference, made his first visit to the school this week! Keeper will be joining the students at the High School once a week, providing support for them as they handle the stresses of high school and adolescence.

Enjoy the video slideshow featuring images of our students enjoying the new, four-legged additions to our team!

post_text: Eleven Sullivan West High School students will have their original stories and poems read by a selection of actors and artists attending the 2019 Deep Water Literary Festival on Sunday, June 23rd at 2:15pm in The Dream Room, 108 Main Street, Narrowsburg. Join us for this free event or stop by The Dream Room at any time during the festival to view the work by these talented students. You will also have the opportunity to make a silent bid on the wonderful, professional artwork accompanying the stories. Some of these proceeds will help fund future creative projects at Sullivan West!
